1
00:00:00,933 --> 00:00:02,200
<i>The changes
in the family constitution</i>

2
00:00:02,333 --> 00:00:03,467
<i> have already been finalized.</i>

3
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:05,767
<i> I'm opening up the opportunity</i>

4
00:00:05,900 --> 00:00:08,533
<i>for all my children
to inherit my position.</i>

5
00:00:08,633 --> 00:00:10,467
<i>I think you still want
to be an heiress.</i>

6
00:00:10,600 --> 00:00:12,200
<i>Since you got
to this earth, Caroline,</i>

7
00:00:12,300 --> 00:00:13,467
<i>you've been ruining
everything.</i>

8
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:15,633
<i>You have a better chance
because you're a suck-up.</i>

9
00:00:15,767 --> 00:00:17,400
<i> I know you hate me,</i>

10
00:00:17,567 --> 00:00:19,300
<i>but is that enough
to have me kidnapped?</i>

11
00:00:19,433 --> 00:00:21,867
<i>She clearly wants
to destroy us!</i>

12
00:00:21,967 --> 00:00:23,233
<i> Character assassination.</i>

13
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:26,567
<i>Caroline, accusing your sister
of having you kidnapped</i>

14
00:00:26,733 --> 00:00:27,867
<i> is just too much!</i>

15
00:00:27,967 --> 00:00:29,067
<i> Even you, Pa.</i>

16
00:00:29,233 --> 00:00:31,233
<i>Maybe you told them
about our new suspect,</i>

17
00:00:31,333 --> 00:00:33,233
<i>but we don't have
real proof, right?</i>

18
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:34,900
<i>So I guess
nobody believed you.</i>

19
00:00:35,033 --> 00:00:35,967
<i> That must feel terrible.</i>

20
00:00:36,100 --> 00:00:39,267
<i>When the people you love
keep hurting you.</i>

21
00:00:39,367 --> 00:00:40,933
<i>I won't waste
my tears on them.</i>

22
00:00:41,033 --> 00:00:42,433
<i> What I need to do right now</i>

23
00:00:42,533 --> 00:00:44,233
<i>is prove to them
that I am right,</i>

24
00:00:44,333 --> 00:00:45,800
<i> that I'm telling the truth.</i>

25
00:00:45,967 --> 00:00:52,767
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

26
00:01:27,833 --> 00:01:28,767
Nanny.

27
00:01:28,967 --> 00:01:31,367
Don't forget to update me
on Irene's whereabouts.

28
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:33,200
I need to know where she goes

29
00:01:33,333 --> 00:01:34,800
and whatever she's up to.

30
00:01:34,967 --> 00:01:36,500
I need to know her next step.

31
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:44,767
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

32
00:01:56,600 --> 00:02:03,667
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

33
00:02:06,067 --> 00:02:11,233
[ENGINE STARTS, REVVING]

34
00:02:11,367 --> 00:02:17,667
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

35
00:02:17,867 --> 00:02:19,867
Thea, please check
if there are any reports

36
00:02:20,033 --> 00:02:21,100
about kidnapping

37
00:02:21,233 --> 00:02:23,567
and if someone's asking
for ransom.

38
00:02:23,733 --> 00:02:25,933
Then let me talk
to the head of security.

39
00:02:27,100 --> 00:02:28,400
Please update me soon.

40
00:02:32,100 --> 00:02:33,333
[GINA] Wilson.

41
00:02:36,067 --> 00:02:38,200
Why did you do this to me?

42
00:02:38,367 --> 00:02:39,267
Do what?

43
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:41,533
You hired another lawyer

44
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:44,267
to accommodate the changes
in the family constitution.

45
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:45,333
Gina, listen.

46
00:02:45,433 --> 00:02:47,000
No! You listen.

47
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:49,333
You always do this to me.

48
00:02:49,467 --> 00:02:51,467
Don't you have
any respect for me?

49
00:02:52,233 --> 00:02:54,300
Not only as the mother
of your son,

50
00:02:54,433 --> 00:02:56,200
but as a human being.

51
00:02:56,300 --> 00:02:58,233
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

52
00:02:58,400 --> 00:02:59,433
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

53
00:03:00,100 --> 00:03:01,433
But I tell you...

54
00:03:02,233 --> 00:03:03,867
I'm not going to give up.

55
00:03:04,433 --> 00:03:06,367
I will make sure

56
00:03:06,467 --> 00:03:08,733
that Carlo inherits everything.

57
00:03:09,633 --> 00:03:11,467
Not only because
he's a good kid,

58
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:12,967
but he's a brilliant kid,

59
00:03:13,100 --> 00:03:15,433
and he deserves only the best.

60
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:21,033
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

61
00:03:23,767 --> 00:03:30,767
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

62
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:45,633
[CAROLINE] Oh.
We should've gone straight.

63
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:47,100
[BINGO] Someone's following us.

64
00:03:47,267 --> 00:03:48,333
What?

65
00:03:49,467 --> 00:03:50,600
Really?

66
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:53,233
Which one?

67
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:54,467
The black one.

68
00:03:56,033 --> 00:03:56,967
Hold tight!

69
00:03:57,133 --> 00:03:58,600
[ENGINE REVVING]

70
00:03:58,700 --> 00:04:04,033
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

71
00:04:04,167 --> 00:04:05,367
[TIRES SCREECH]

72
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:13,133
[GROANS]

73
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:16,133
I knew it!

74
00:04:17,333 --> 00:04:19,000
This is all Irene's doing.

75
00:04:19,167 --> 00:04:21,467
She knew I was coming home,
so she had someone follow me.

76
00:04:21,633 --> 00:04:22,633
And she's not going to stop

77
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,467
until she gets what she wants.

78
00:04:24,633 --> 00:04:27,933
- [STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]
- [BREATHING HEAVILY]

79
00:04:29,933 --> 00:04:32,400
Do you really think
your sister is the culprit...

80
00:04:33,433 --> 00:04:35,000
and your father
doesn't believe you?

81
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:37,667
Stay low for now.

82
00:04:38,700 --> 00:04:39,833
Wait until things
cool down.

83
00:04:41,433 --> 00:04:43,000
You need to gather
allies first.

84
00:04:43,167 --> 00:04:50,000
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

85
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:57,033
Oh well, come to think of it.

86
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:58,567
It's good you weren't here.

87
00:04:58,700 --> 00:05:00,733
It was such a mess.

88
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:01,733
Yeah.

89
00:05:01,933 --> 00:05:04,333
I'll tell you everything
when you come back.

90
00:05:04,433 --> 00:05:06,200
Okay. I have to go.

91
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:07,867
Just always be prepared, okay?

92
00:05:09,233 --> 00:05:10,167
Hey.

93
00:05:12,267 --> 00:05:13,500
How is Cindy?

94
00:05:14,967 --> 00:05:15,933
She's okay.

95
00:05:16,067 --> 00:05:18,067
It was just because
of high blood pressure.

96
00:05:18,233 --> 00:05:19,667
That's understandable.

97
00:05:19,767 --> 00:05:21,667
Make her take
some garlic.

98
00:05:21,767 --> 00:05:23,500
The family physician
is attending to her.

99
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,867
Thank you anyway.

100
00:05:25,033 --> 00:05:26,067
Excuse me.

101
00:05:26,233 --> 00:05:33,067
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

102
00:05:36,233 --> 00:05:37,100
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

103
00:05:43,467 --> 00:05:45,467
You must not
go outside alone.

104
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:47,567
It's too dangerous.

105
00:05:47,667 --> 00:05:50,200
Plus, I don't want to drag
my family into your mess.

106
00:05:50,300 --> 00:05:51,433
Exactly.

107
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:52,633
This is my problem.

108
00:05:52,767 --> 00:05:54,100
I should just leave.

109
00:05:54,967 --> 00:05:56,200
No.

110
00:05:56,300 --> 00:05:57,700
Then what should I do?

111
00:05:57,800 --> 00:06:00,533
How am I supposed
to find allies

112
00:06:00,633 --> 00:06:02,100
- if I'm stuck here?
- Me.

113
00:06:03,433 --> 00:06:04,733
You have me.

114
00:06:05,467 --> 00:06:06,567
I'll help you.

115
00:06:06,733 --> 00:06:09,800
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

116
00:06:09,967 --> 00:06:12,267
We've already made it
this far anyway.

117
00:06:13,300 --> 00:06:15,267
It's our problem now.

118
00:06:15,367 --> 00:06:16,667
[NENE] Hey! I heard that.

119
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:18,733
What "problem"
are you talking about?

120
00:06:18,833 --> 00:06:21,300
I told you to stay
away from trouble!

121
00:06:21,467 --> 00:06:22,600
Wait. Calm down.

122
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:24,267
I'm helping her
with a problem.

123
00:06:24,367 --> 00:06:25,767
[MONCHING] Are you
hiding something?

124
00:06:25,867 --> 00:06:27,633
She can't go home yet.

125
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:30,267
Why?

126
00:06:30,367 --> 00:06:32,100
[MONCHING] Why can't
you go home?

127
00:06:32,267 --> 00:06:33,733
Is your life in danger?

128
00:06:36,167 --> 00:06:37,600
My parents are...

129
00:06:42,233 --> 00:06:44,033
getting a divorce.

130
00:06:44,167 --> 00:06:44,967
Huh?

131
00:06:45,167 --> 00:06:47,633
That's why I don't want
to go home yet.

132
00:06:47,733 --> 00:06:49,267
- [BINGO CLEARS THROAT]
- [NENE] Um...

133
00:06:49,367 --> 00:06:51,600
Ling, dear, come here.

134
00:06:51,700 --> 00:06:54,433
Are you hungry?
Do you want to eat?

135
00:06:54,533 --> 00:06:55,967
Have a seat.

136
00:06:56,067 --> 00:06:58,200
I'll prepare some food
for you.

137
00:07:04,700 --> 00:07:06,367
They got away again.

138
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:07,633
Don't worry.

139
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:11,700
It won't be long
until we find them.

140
00:07:11,833 --> 00:07:18,800
- [STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]
- [PHONE RINGING]

141
00:07:21,667 --> 00:07:22,800
Hello, Pa?

142
00:07:23,433 --> 00:07:25,167
<i> Where are you?</i>

143
00:07:25,267 --> 00:07:27,000
<i> Come home and let's eat.</i>

144
00:07:27,167 --> 00:07:28,233
Okay, Pa.

145
00:07:28,367 --> 00:07:33,700
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

146
00:07:42,867 --> 00:07:44,633
- Where are you going?
- To a party.

147
00:07:44,733 --> 00:07:46,567
Nobody is leaving
the house.

148
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:48,500
Especially you
and Bettina.

149
00:07:48,700 --> 00:07:49,900
What?

150
00:07:50,067 --> 00:07:51,533
Why me?

151
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:53,500
It's because of Caroline's
alleged kidnapping.

152
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:54,533
That's enough.

153
00:07:54,633 --> 00:07:57,700
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

154
00:07:57,867 --> 00:08:01,700
The changes in the constitution
I discussed earlier

155
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:04,567
will give equal
opportunity to--

156
00:08:04,733 --> 00:08:06,867
It's because everything I do
is for the family.

157
00:08:07,700 --> 00:08:08,867
Irene.

158
00:08:08,967 --> 00:08:09,933
What?

159
00:08:10,067 --> 00:08:11,100
It's true, Ma.

160
00:08:12,567 --> 00:08:14,367
"Equal opportunity?"

161
00:08:14,533 --> 00:08:17,267
[CHUCKLES WRYLY] I don't even
matter to this family.

162
00:08:18,967 --> 00:08:20,767
But don't worry,
Ma and Pa.

163
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:22,767
You'll find me useful
someday.

164
00:08:23,767 --> 00:08:25,300
You're all going to need me.

165
00:08:25,433 --> 00:08:32,267
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

166
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:42,733
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

167
00:08:42,833 --> 00:08:43,900
[CINDY] Caroline.

168
00:08:44,967 --> 00:08:46,900
<i>You have to accept
the truth.</i>

169
00:08:47,933 --> 00:08:50,033
<i>I know you don't
understand this yet,</i>

170
00:08:50,133 --> 00:08:53,200
<i>but your mom
ended her own life.</i>

171
00:08:53,833 --> 00:08:55,633
<i> That's a lie.</i>

172
00:08:56,633 --> 00:08:57,833
[CINDY] Wilson.

173
00:08:58,667 --> 00:08:59,933
<i> You should talk to her.</i>

174
00:09:00,033 --> 00:09:03,267
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

175
00:09:03,433 --> 00:09:04,433
<i> Ling.</i> [EXHALES DEEPLY]

176
00:09:04,533 --> 00:09:07,500
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

177
00:09:07,633 --> 00:09:09,433
<i> I'm really, really sorry.</i>

178
00:09:09,533 --> 00:09:13,967
[SOBBING] No. No. No.

179
00:09:14,133 --> 00:09:18,100
[SOBBING]

180
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,500
<i> I'm sorry, Ling.</i>

181
00:09:19,633 --> 00:09:23,167
- [MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [SOBBING]

182
00:09:23,300 --> 00:09:25,733
[YOUNG CAROLINE] No. No.

183
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:28,300
[GASPS]

184
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:36,367
[BREATH QUIVERING]

185
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:50,800
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

186
00:09:50,900 --> 00:09:52,000
- Excuse me.
- [MAN] Yes?

187
00:09:52,167 --> 00:09:54,500
- Can we ask you something?
- What is it?

188
00:09:54,667 --> 00:09:56,533
Do you know someone
here named Mark?

189
00:09:56,667 --> 00:09:59,000
Mark? Let me see.

190
00:09:59,167 --> 00:10:00,833
There are lots of people
named Mark here.

191
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:03,133
How about Mark Santos?

192
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:04,400
Oh, Mark Santos.

193
00:10:05,367 --> 00:10:06,567
He's not here anymore.

194
00:10:06,700 --> 00:10:08,133
What do you mean?

195
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:12,667
He moved out when some
guys caused a commotion.

196
00:10:12,767 --> 00:10:15,133
- A commotion?
- Yes.

197
00:10:15,233 --> 00:10:19,000
They said one of them
was from Barangay 143.

198
00:10:19,100 --> 00:10:23,200
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

199
00:10:23,367 --> 00:10:25,367
- Okay. Thank you, mister.
- Thank you.

200
00:10:25,533 --> 00:10:29,367
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

201
00:10:29,533 --> 00:10:32,500
You see,
here in Barangay 143,

202
00:10:32,667 --> 00:10:34,000
we spread good vibes.

203
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:36,100
We all love each other here.

204
00:10:36,233 --> 00:10:38,200
You should patch things up.

205
00:10:38,300 --> 00:10:40,367
The next time you
have another misunderstanding...

206
00:10:41,067 --> 00:10:42,400
just come to me, okay?

207
00:10:42,567 --> 00:10:45,700
I'm always ready to listen
if you need some advice.

208
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:47,267
You can tell me anything.

209
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:48,700
Bingo! Excuse me.

210
00:10:48,867 --> 00:10:51,367
Bingo! Bingo! Bingo! Bingo!

211
00:10:51,533 --> 00:10:52,833
- Wait.
- Yes, Chairman?

212
00:10:52,933 --> 00:10:55,033
How is your friend doing?

213
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:57,433
- I heard you two always...
- Always what?

214
00:10:57,567 --> 00:10:59,367
I heard you two
always go out.

215
00:10:59,533 --> 00:11:01,433
Uh, it's... [CHUCKLES]

216
00:11:01,567 --> 00:11:05,067
Well, we have nothing to do
at home, so we go out.

217
00:11:05,233 --> 00:11:07,000
[CHUCKLES] You have a point.

218
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:11,100
By the way Bingo,
we're going to have

219
00:11:11,267 --> 00:11:14,733
a free consultation program for
pregnant women this Sunday.

220
00:11:14,833 --> 00:11:16,900
- For pregnant women?
- Yes.

221
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:19,567
Why are you telling me
this, Chairman?

222
00:11:19,733 --> 00:11:21,067
It will help you a lot.

223
00:11:21,233 --> 00:11:23,633
I don't think it will help me.

224
00:11:23,767 --> 00:11:25,933
Other people need that help,
but I don't.

225
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:27,200
I'll go now, Chairman.

226
00:11:27,300 --> 00:11:29,067
- Take care. Let's go.
- Hi, Chairman!

227
00:11:29,233 --> 00:11:30,700
- Chairman!
- Let's go!

228
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:33,900
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

229
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,567
- Well?
- Come on, please.

230
00:11:35,733 --> 00:11:37,233
No more fighting, okay?

231
00:11:49,100 --> 00:11:50,567
Good morning!

232
00:11:50,667 --> 00:11:52,067
Have some breakfast.

233
00:11:52,167 --> 00:11:53,767
Grandma Nene, have you
seen my clothes?

234
00:11:53,933 --> 00:11:57,467
Monching took them
to have them washed.

235
00:11:57,633 --> 00:12:00,667
What?! Some of them aren't
supposed to be washed.

236
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:02,833
But your clothes might
get moldy.

237
00:12:02,967 --> 00:12:04,467
Where is he?

238
00:12:04,633 --> 00:12:06,100
He's at the rooftop.

239
00:12:07,767 --> 00:12:08,833
Wait!

240
00:12:10,767 --> 00:12:15,800
[PANTING]

241
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:18,300
No, no, no, no, no!

242
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:19,633
Please stop!

243
00:12:19,733 --> 00:12:20,833
- Just stop.
- Huh?

244
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,700
But I'm not done yet.

245
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:24,700
No, it's okay.
It's okay.

246
00:12:24,833 --> 00:12:27,300
Just don't touch it.

247
00:12:27,467 --> 00:12:29,633
Are you sure?
They will smell bad.

248
00:12:30,567 --> 00:12:31,967
Let him be.

249
00:12:32,067 --> 00:12:33,133
He's good at it.

250
00:12:33,300 --> 00:12:34,667
[MONCHING] It's my
part-time job.

251
00:12:34,833 --> 00:12:37,433
I appreciate the gesture but...

252
00:12:38,567 --> 00:12:39,967
my clothes are delicate.

253
00:12:41,033 --> 00:12:44,300
- [NENE] Oh.
- I'll just do it myself.

254
00:12:44,467 --> 00:12:46,800
[NENE] Alright then.
Leave it to her.

255
00:12:46,967 --> 00:12:49,667
She said they're expensive
and delicate.

256
00:12:49,867 --> 00:12:51,900
Go ahead
and wash them yourself.

257
00:12:52,033 --> 00:12:54,367
- You do it.
- Alright.

258
00:12:54,533 --> 00:12:58,167
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

259
00:12:58,333 --> 00:12:59,200
Okay.

260
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:02,467
Y-You want me
to do it?

261
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:05,367
[CAROLINE] It's okay. I...

262
00:13:05,533 --> 00:13:07,633
Are you sure?

263
00:13:09,033 --> 00:13:10,200
I can manage.

264
00:13:11,333 --> 00:13:12,233
Oh.

265
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:14,800
Okay. She said
she can manage.

266
00:13:14,900 --> 00:13:16,833
Okay, fine.
We'll leave you there.

267
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:18,833
- Can she really do it?
- Let's just go.

268
00:13:18,933 --> 00:13:19,900
[MONCHING] Alright then.

269
00:13:20,033 --> 00:13:27,067
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

270
00:13:39,100 --> 00:13:41,533
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

271
00:13:41,633 --> 00:13:48,433
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

272
00:14:08,900 --> 00:14:11,867
I thought our partnership
with the Liaos is on hold?

273
00:14:11,967 --> 00:14:12,900
Look.

274
00:14:13,067 --> 00:14:14,300
Why did they suddenly
e-mail us

275
00:14:14,433 --> 00:14:16,400
about the conditions
they want on the contract?

276
00:14:17,433 --> 00:14:18,633
Hmm...

277
00:14:18,767 --> 00:14:20,100
So...

278
00:14:20,267 --> 00:14:22,100
they're pushing through
with the partnership?

279
00:14:23,067 --> 00:14:27,233
Does that mean they no longer
need the public apology?

280
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:30,467
Well, I honestly think
they're taking advantage of us.

281
00:14:30,633 --> 00:14:34,267
They want more shares
and more profits.

282
00:14:34,367 --> 00:14:35,933
[SCOFFS]

283
00:14:36,100 --> 00:14:38,467
Come to think of it,
they'll profit more

284
00:14:38,633 --> 00:14:41,733
if we build malls
on their properties.

285
00:14:41,833 --> 00:14:43,933
What? All because
of the Ting Hun?

286
00:14:44,100 --> 00:14:45,567
Maybe.

287
00:14:45,667 --> 00:14:50,133
Or maybe they're doing something
behind our backs.

288
00:14:50,300 --> 00:14:54,167
They either want us to
accept the offer or back out.

289
00:14:54,300 --> 00:15:01,333
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

290
00:15:03,367 --> 00:15:06,033
[ALBERT] I'll make
Charleston pay.

291
00:15:06,167 --> 00:15:08,467
Especially Wilson!

292
00:15:08,633 --> 00:15:11,633
(In Chinese)
They can't do this to us!

293
00:15:11,733 --> 00:15:14,033
This is all Edward's fault.

294
00:15:14,167 --> 00:15:15,467
(In Chinese)
What were you thinking?!

295
00:15:15,633 --> 00:15:18,367
Who's that Liv woman that
you'd chose her over Bettina?

296
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:20,300
They even have
a photo evidence.

297
00:15:20,467 --> 00:15:23,133
[HUFFS] That he can easily deny.

298
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:26,667
I can't believe I'm hearing this
from you, Albert.

299
00:15:27,567 --> 00:15:30,033
Well, Bettina and
Edward's marriage

300
00:15:30,167 --> 00:15:34,800
is just a business transaction
in the first place.

301
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,833
But Bettina loves Edward.

302
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:41,500
Love is secondary here.

303
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:44,333
It's more important
that we get

304
00:15:44,433 --> 00:15:47,500
a better business deal
with Wilson.

305
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:50,800
[ALBERT HUFFS,
BREATHES DEEPLY]

306
00:15:50,900 --> 00:15:54,633
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

307
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:00,200
Well?

308
00:16:00,367 --> 00:16:02,233
I can't find Mark.

309
00:16:03,867 --> 00:16:06,367
As long as they're out there,
they'll come after Ling.

310
00:16:07,367 --> 00:16:08,700
I'm having goosebumps.

311
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:11,900
What if someone
followed her here?

312
00:16:12,067 --> 00:16:13,500
I know, right?

313
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:16,100
The two of us could
also get in trouble.

314
00:16:17,433 --> 00:16:18,867
There's one more thing
I'm worried about.

315
00:16:19,933 --> 00:16:22,100
What if my family gets dragged
into this mess?

316
00:16:24,267 --> 00:16:26,367
We need to find a new lead.

317
00:16:28,300 --> 00:16:29,900
Chill, dude.

318
00:16:30,067 --> 00:16:33,033
I'm not called "Snoop"
for nothing.

319
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:34,333
What?

320
00:16:35,867 --> 00:16:37,900
I'll try snooping around
Mark's place again.

321
00:16:38,067 --> 00:16:39,267
[ENGINE STARTING]

322
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:41,733
Maybe I'll find something.

323
00:16:43,267 --> 00:16:44,467
This is the last time, okay?

324
00:16:45,767 --> 00:16:46,900
But I'll go with you.

325
00:16:47,067 --> 00:16:48,233
Alright! [CHUCKLES]

326
00:16:48,333 --> 00:16:50,733
- [BINGO SIGHS]
- Then let's go!

327
00:16:50,833 --> 00:16:57,600
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

328
00:16:57,767 --> 00:16:58,733
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

329
00:16:58,900 --> 00:17:01,233
[DARA SINGING]

330
00:17:05,900 --> 00:17:08,533
Oh, is that the girl?

331
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:11,633
[SIGHS]

332
00:17:13,133 --> 00:17:14,733
What a surprise!

333
00:17:16,033 --> 00:17:17,433
She's doing the laundry.

334
00:17:17,533 --> 00:17:24,600
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

335
00:17:28,167 --> 00:17:29,667
[KNOCKS ON DOOR]

336
00:17:33,633 --> 00:17:34,767
Ling?

337
00:17:36,700 --> 00:17:37,600
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

338
00:17:38,467 --> 00:17:41,333
Ling, I know you're sad

339
00:17:41,467 --> 00:17:43,933
because of what happened
to your clothes.

340
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:47,133
But, don't worry.

341
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:49,233
I brought you some clothes

342
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:51,867
from my stall.

343
00:17:53,067 --> 00:17:57,200
They might not look that fancy,

344
00:17:57,333 --> 00:17:59,333
but they're decent.

345
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:03,433
I'll just leave them here.

346
00:18:07,033 --> 00:18:09,467
Cheer up, okay?

347
00:18:19,033 --> 00:18:25,867
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

348
00:18:39,867 --> 00:18:46,667
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

349
00:18:59,467 --> 00:19:01,600
- [SNOOP] Thank you, miss.
- He's about this tall.

350
00:19:01,733 --> 00:19:03,433
And he's skinny.

351
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:05,733
Excuse me, can I
ask a question?

352
00:19:05,867 --> 00:19:07,367
Do you know Mark?

353
00:19:07,467 --> 00:19:08,900
- Mark, the baldy?
- Yeah!

354
00:19:09,033 --> 00:19:10,533
I-I'm friends with him.

355
00:19:10,633 --> 00:19:12,567
Why are there so many people
looking for Mark?

356
00:19:12,700 --> 00:19:15,833
A man also asked my husband
about Mark's whereabouts.

357
00:19:15,967 --> 00:19:17,600
But I heard Mark's been missing

358
00:19:17,767 --> 00:19:20,933
ever since he got in a fight
with someone from Village 143.

359
00:19:21,067 --> 00:19:22,333
Miss.

360
00:19:22,467 --> 00:19:23,700
Someone else is
looking for him?

361
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:24,767
Yes.

362
00:19:24,933 --> 00:19:26,233
W-Wait a minute.

363
00:19:26,367 --> 00:19:27,933
Does he know the person
Mark fought with

364
00:19:28,100 --> 00:19:28,967
was from Village 143?

365
00:19:29,133 --> 00:19:30,800
Yes, my husband told him.

366
00:19:30,967 --> 00:19:32,800
What did the man look like?

367
00:19:32,933 --> 00:19:34,633
Oh, he was very handsome.

368
00:19:34,767 --> 00:19:37,267
You took a picture of that guy
who was looking for Mark, right?

369
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:39,133
- Let me see it.
- Can we see?

370
00:19:39,267 --> 00:19:41,033
Sure, hold on.
Hey, hurry up!

371
00:19:41,167 --> 00:19:43,133
Here. Look at him.

372
00:19:43,267 --> 00:19:44,800
Isn't he handsome?

373
00:19:46,233 --> 00:19:52,467
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

374
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:53,633
He's not that handsome.

375
00:19:53,767 --> 00:19:54,967
[WOMAN] What are
you talking about?

376
00:19:55,133 --> 00:19:56,267
Just look at that face!

377
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:58,400
Dude, he's that guy.

378
00:19:58,500 --> 00:20:00,733
The one who's been
tailing us.

379
00:20:00,833 --> 00:20:01,933
Crap.

380
00:20:02,100 --> 00:20:06,500
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

381
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:10,800
These are vitamins
for pregnant women.

382
00:20:12,033 --> 00:20:14,600
Tell everyone in town

383
00:20:14,700 --> 00:20:17,333
that we're giving away
free vitamins

384
00:20:17,467 --> 00:20:19,433
to everyone who'll come
for a consultation.

385
00:20:19,533 --> 00:20:20,500
[ALL] Yes, Chairman.

386
00:20:20,667 --> 00:20:22,333
- Way to go!
- You're the best!

387
00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:24,733
- [MAN] You're amazing.
- I know, right? [CHUCKLES]

388
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:28,500
Here.

389
00:20:28,633 --> 00:20:31,000
We have more stocks left.

390
00:20:31,167 --> 00:20:33,000
Good day, Chairman.

391
00:20:33,167 --> 00:20:35,267
Good day to you, too.

392
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:37,333
How can I help you?

393
00:20:37,467 --> 00:20:42,333
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

394
00:20:42,467 --> 00:20:44,133
<i> I brought you some clothes.</i>

395
00:20:44,233 --> 00:20:46,033
<i>They may not look
that fancy,</i>

396
00:20:46,167 --> 00:20:47,667
<i> but they're decent.</i>

397
00:20:47,800 --> 00:20:49,767
<i> Is Ling at home?</i>

398
00:20:49,900 --> 00:20:51,533
<i>I haven't seen her.
Maybe she went out.</i>

399
00:20:51,667 --> 00:20:53,033
<i>So many people
are looking for Mark.</i>

400
00:20:53,200 --> 00:20:54,533
<i> What did he look like?</i>

401
00:20:54,667 --> 00:20:56,133
<i>He's that guy
who's been tailing us.</i>

402
00:20:56,233 --> 00:20:57,367
<i> This is getting dangerous.</i>

403
00:20:57,533 --> 00:20:59,000
<i> We should get bodyguards.</i>

404
00:20:59,133 --> 00:21:00,033
<i> It's this car.</i>

405
00:21:00,167 --> 00:21:01,367
<i> They're really after Ling.</i>

406
00:21:01,533 --> 00:21:02,767
<i> We need to find Ling.</i>

407
00:21:02,900 --> 00:21:04,700
<i>You search upstairs!
I'll search this floor!</i>

408
00:21:04,833 --> 00:21:05,867
<i> Ling? Ling?</i>

409
00:21:06,033 --> 00:21:06,933
<i> She's not here.</i>

410
00:21:07,067 --> 00:21:08,000
<i> She's not here either.</i>
